Plate type description object

root Plate Plate allOf PlateData plateType name
Type: string

The name of the plate type.
Example:

"Greiner 1-drop square"

root Plate Plate allOf PlateData plateType numberRows
Type: integer

The number of rows in the plate. For a typical 96-well plate, this will be 8.

Value must be strictly greater than 0

root Plate Plate allOf PlateData plateType numberColumns
Type: integer

The number of columns in the plate. For a typical 96-well plate, this will be 12.

Value must be strictly greater than 0

root Plate Plate allOf PlateData plateType numberSubPositions
Type: integer

The number of sub-wells in the plate. For in-situ plates with no dividers, this should be the actual number of drops dispensed.

Value must be strictly greater than 0

root Plate Plate allOf PlateData plateType dropMapping
Type: string

<p>The sender's numbering of the sub-wells. This can be used by the receiver to map the sender's well numbering onto their own.<p><p>It is an error if the sender and receiver disagree on the basic geometry (e.g., three drops across the top with a reservoir underneath). However, they can disagree on the drop order; this property is intended to help overcome such disagreements.</p>
Examples:

"123,RRR"

"23,1R"

root PlateWell PlateWell allOf PlateWellData rowNumber
Type: integer

<The row number of this well. This is 1-based, so row A is 1, row H is 8. This should be validated against the plateType's rows property.

Value must be strictly greater than 0

root PlateWell PlateWell allOf PlateWellData columnNumber
Type: integer

<The column number of this well. This is 1-based, so should match the column labels on the plate. This should be validated against the plateType's columns property.

Value must be strictly greater than 0

root PlateWell PlateWell allOf PlateWellData name
Type: string

A human-friendly well identifier. If present, this should be validated to ensure that it refers to the correct row and column.
Examples:

"H1"

"C03"

 Must match regular expression: ^[0-9]{4}-(0[1-9]|1[0-2])-(0[1-9]|[12][0-9]|3[01])T([01][0-9]|2[0-3]):[0-5][0-9]:[0-5][0-9](\.[0-9]+)?(Z|[+-]([01][0-9]|2[0-3]):[0-5][0-9])$
